            "answer_text": "If you sign into Google Chrome , you have access to Google books. During account creation they ask for a credit card /debit card. Now , once the account is created ad you sign in to Google Books, they have books marked as Free . Just click on the books which are marked free and click on price and the book gets downloaded to your Google Book Reader. You can choose to build a library using the Google Account etc. When a free book is downloaded, you will get a meaage from Google Wallet. Don\u2019t freak out. For free books, the message simply says that Rs. 0.00 have been deducted from your account. So despite Google having your credit card account it doesn\u2019t deduct money for free books . ",
